    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I think an optional project-level `network-config.yaml` makes sense. For example I have an HTTP API app, which I deploy on Heroku and I have trouble configuring the app to connect to a network different from Infura.\r\n\r\nThe current config allows only for setting `WEB3_INFURA_PROJECT_ID`. I am trying to make the app agnostic to Infura, so a config `HTTP_RPC_URL` makes more sense in my case, but with the current network management it's hard to achieve this. The only approach I can think of is to package the app with docker and put a special `network-config.yaml` in the home folder of the docker image.",
