    "body": "I think I found another use case, that justifies to add this kind of functionality.\r\n\r\nI created a docker-compose config for the ganache blockchain, so everybody can see and reuse it quickly in my project, and I would like to add that ganache chain to brownie via the configuration file  (which is not possible atm) to configure default connectivity to my dockerized ganache network by ONLY setting the RPC url (which is also not possible at the moment for development networks, only `cmd` attribute is supported).\r\n\r\nThis approach would be declarative and explicit for other onboarding developers, how the system is set up.\r\n\r\nWhat do you guys think?",
